(569, 3, '2014-03-13 02:57:11', '2014-03-13 07:57:11', '<h2>Epilogue - "The USA Experiment"</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_04a_Close_Experiment.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Summary</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_04b_Close_FINAL.mp4"][/video]', 'The SalesMind Epilogue & Summary', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '544-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-13 02:57:11', '2014-03-13 07:57:11', '', 544, 'http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/544-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(570, 3, '2014-03-13 02:57:48', '2014-03-13 07:57:48', '<h2>Introduction - "The USA Experiment"</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_00a_The_Experiment.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Doug''s Start with Lanier Business Products</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_00b_DT_Start.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Origin of The SalesMind Concept</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_00c_SM_Concept-Origin.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>What Is A "SalesMind?"</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_00d_What_Is_The_SM.mp4"][/video]', 'The SalesMind Introduction', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '546-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-13 02:57:48', '2014-03-13 07:57:48', '', 546, 'http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/546-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(571, 3, '2014-03-13 02:58:44', '2014-03-13 07:58:44', '<h2>Part I - Desire</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_01a_Intro-Overview.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR PART I: DESIRE</strong>\r\n<strong>1)</strong> Focus is the concentration of desire\r\n<strong>2)</strong> Purpose is the motive of desire\r\n<strong>3)</strong> Action is the execution of desire\r\n<strong>4)</strong> Response is the test of desire\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 1 - FOCUS</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_01b_Point_01_Focus.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 1: FOCUS</strong>\r\n<strong>1)</strong> All other <em>SalesMind</em> skills rely on focus (intense and sustained concentration)\r\n<strong>2)</strong> You become what you concentrate on most—positive or negative\r\n<strong>3)</strong> Successful selling occurs when your focus causes the buyer to focus on your offering\r\n<strong>4)</strong> “Wide” focus is the ability to keep things in perspective\r\n<strong>5)</strong> Don’t over-focus on the external world or other people to dictate your destiny\r\n<strong>6)</strong> Be able to change your immediate focus to change your state of mind\r\n<strong>7)</strong> Develop and enrich a “positive emotional inventory”\r\n<strong>8)</strong> Diminish and weaken negative emotions from the past or present—or fear of the future\r\n<strong>9)</strong> You must be able to convert instantly negative emotions back to positive\r\n<strong>10)</strong> Focus most on the things in life that have the greatest Purpose\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 2 - PURPOSE</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_01c_Point_02_Purpose.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 2: PURPOSE</strong>\r\n<strong>1)</strong> Purpose is the answer to “why” you do things—and what you will sacrifice most for\r\n<strong>2) </strong>Write down the top purposes in your life now and for later\r\n<strong>3) </strong>Giving service that has value is the most important purpose in selling\r\n<strong>4) </strong>The derivatives of your purpose should be your identities, beliefs, values, and goals\r\n<strong>5) </strong>Great purpose is fueled when you can create some balance in your life\r\n<strong>6) </strong>Transition your current identities to your desired identities\r\n<strong>7) </strong>Define on paper what you believe in and what you don’t believe in\r\n<strong>8) </strong>Define on paper your personal value system\r\n<strong>9) </strong>Write down, update, and measure your goals\r\n<strong>10) </strong>Defining your purpose(s) becomes the reasons you sell and work hard for success\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 3 - ACTION</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_01d1_Point_03_Action.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 3: ACTION</strong>\r\n<strong>1) </strong>Act now and control the only moment you can—now\r\n<strong>2) </strong>Action with knowledge, skill, and speed is the ultimate competitive advantage\r\n<strong>3) </strong>The challenges to taking action are endless\r\n<strong>4) </strong>Do what you don’t like to do\r\n<strong>5) </strong>Action creates an accumulation of unknown, positive results\r\n<strong>6) </strong>Let your defined beliefs fuel your actions\r\n<strong>7) </strong>Allocate your actions starting with those that have the highest priority and most impact\r\n<strong>8) </strong>Follow-up actions in sales separate the winners from the losers\r\n<strong>9) </strong>Action is the only cure for a sales or emotional slump\r\n<strong>10) </strong>You will die one day, so take as many actions now while you have time to succeed\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>What Was The Most Memorable Day of ACTION?</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_01d2_Point_03_Action_(story).mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 4 - RESPONSE</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_01e_Point_04_Response.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 4: RESPONSE</strong>\r\n<strong>1) </strong>Your desires and purposes will be tested to see if you respond\r\n<strong>2) </strong>Pressure and resistance are constant forces in life for any winner—or loser\r\n<strong>3) </strong>Learn how to respond the right way and not the wrong way\r\n<strong>4) </strong>Responding to pain and personal adversity are fundamental to any success\r\n<strong>5) </strong>Those who master sales understand it is a response business\r\n<strong>6) </strong>Fear is the most powerful enemy to respond to—so do it quickly\r\n<strong>7) </strong>Master the mindsets that enable you to overcome anything\r\n<strong>8) </strong>You must learn the exact words and use them for the objections you face in sales\r\n<strong>9) </strong>You must learn immediately how to respond to the objection of high price\r\n<strong>10) </strong>Respond with the right words, under pressure, and when there is money on the line', 'The SalesMind Part 1', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '548-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-13 02:58:44', '2014-03-13 07:58:44', '', 548, 'http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/548-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(572, 3, '2014-03-13 02:59:56', '2014-03-13 07:59:56', '<h2>Part II - Persuasion</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_02a_Intro-Overview.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR PART II: PERSUASION</strong>\r\n<strong>1)</strong> Connection is the pathway to persuasion\r\n<strong>2)</strong> Value is the engine of persuasion\r\n<strong>3)</strong> Urgency is the effect of persuasion\r\n<strong>4)</strong> Leverage is the price of persuasion\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 5 - CONNECTION</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_02b_Point_05_Connection.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 5: CONNECTION</strong>\r\n<strong>1) </strong>Communicate effectively to move a buyer from indifference to trust—trust is the goal\r\n<strong>2) </strong>People buy from those they like—so be likable like an “old shoe”\r\n<strong>3) </strong>Learn and master the progressive stages of connection with buyers\r\n<strong>4) </strong>Pure connection always presents problems to overcome\r\n<strong>5) </strong>You must learn which role to assume at which time to gain the best connection\r\n<strong>6) </strong>Better character is the foundation of better connection\r\n<strong>7) </strong>You are paid the most for “credible judgment”\r\n<strong>8) </strong>Be able to communicate sharply, quickly, energetically, and with a strong vocabulary\r\n<strong>9) </strong>Master the sequence of connection: Input, Translation, and Output\r\n<strong>10) </strong>Reconnection (follow-up) always is a winning recipe—always do more than your competitor\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 6 - VALUE</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_02c_Point_06_Value.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 6: VALUE</strong>\r\n<strong>1) </strong>Your understanding and articulation of value to the buyer is the basis of your income\r\n<strong>2) </strong>Buyers are well-trained and want the most value (benefit) for the least money\r\n<strong>3) </strong>You must believe the value of your product or service far outweighs the price of it\r\n<strong>4) </strong>Learn the four basic reasons why buyers spend money\r\n<strong>5) </strong>A customer’s view of value is different than a prospect’s\r\n<strong>6) </strong>Universal Value is how a purchase fits any buyer’s general view of reward and pain\r\n<strong>7) </strong>Specific Business Value is the exact detail of what your offering does for the buyer\r\n<strong>8) </strong>Personal Life Value is what a purchase really does to enhance the buyer’s life\r\n<strong>9) </strong>Credibility Value is why you are the expert—and you can prove it with customer facts\r\n<strong>10) </strong>Uniqueness Value is why you are the only choice as a seller—different and better\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 7 - URGENCY</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_02d_Point_07_Urgency.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 7: URGENCY</strong>\r\n<strong>1) </strong>Persuading buyers to purchase now rather than later is a world-class selling skill\r\n<strong>2) </strong>Buyers need to have either a disturbing problem (pain) or intense desire to buy now\r\n<strong>3) </strong>You should never be afraid of the buyer if you are a credible person\r\n<strong>4) </strong>Learn to detect a buyer’s urgency both before and after your interactions\r\n<strong>5) </strong>Stimulating buyer urgency has degrees of difficulty relative to each potential sale\r\n<strong>6) </strong>Learn and respond to the four reasons buyers don’t want to buy now\r\n<strong>7) </strong>The key in the buyer’s mind is the benefit of the immediate transaction to them\r\n<strong>8) </strong>Discover all “natural urgencies” you can to create a transaction now\r\n<strong>9) </strong>Learn to apply any “enhanced urgencies” you need to create a transaction now\r\n<strong>10) </strong>Your own self-urgency and the speed of your work are inseparable from success\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 8 - LEVERAGE</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_02e_Point_08_Leverage.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 8: LEVERAGE</strong>\r\n<strong>1) </strong>Leverage is the strength and value of your position as a seller at any given moment\r\n<strong>2) </strong>Your price secured depends upon the leverage you establish with the buyer\r\n<strong>3) </strong>Degree of your leverage equals the sum of your connection, value, and urgency\r\n<strong>4) </strong>You must orchestrate both Cumulative leverage and Cooperation leverage\r\n<strong>5) </strong>“Deep” leverage is your position of strength and value with any one buyer\r\n<strong>6) </strong>“Wide” leverage is your position of strength from assembling a large number of  buyers\r\n<strong>7) </strong>Define every possible value component (lever) and assess its strength or weakness\r\n<strong>8) </strong>Master every angle of how to gain price leverage\r\n<strong>9) </strong>Master all of the five negotiation dynamics\r\n<strong>10) </strong>Always establish the transaction sequence:  Position to Negotiation to Transaction', 'The SalesMind Part 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '550-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-13 02:59:56', '2014-03-13 07:59:56', '', 550, 'http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/550-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(573, 3, '2014-03-13 03:00:39', '2014-03-13 08:00:39', '<h2>Part III - Timing</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_03a_Intro-Overview.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR PART III: TIMING</strong>\r\n<strong>1)</strong> Priority is the object of your timing\r\n<strong>2)</strong> Control is the flow of timing\r\n<strong>3)</strong> Coverage is the scope of timing\r\n<strong>4)</strong> Adjustment is the change of timing\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 9 - PRIORITY</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_03b_Point_09_Priority.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 9: PRIORITY</strong>\r\n<strong>1) </strong>Pursue the most profitable opportunities with your available time, and the rest can wait\r\n<strong>2) </strong>Define and apply the key operating principles that will drive your priority decisions\r\n<strong>3) </strong>Your priorities in effect are a Constitution for your time, talent, and energy\r\n<strong>4) </strong>Expect a ROI from buyers, company activities, and personal enrichment\r\n<strong>5) </strong>Sticking to effective priorities is confronted with roadblocks every moment\r\n<strong>6) </strong>Clarify and rank your highest revenue sources in both customers and prospects\r\n<strong>7) </strong>You have to factor in flex time and learn to say “no” to stay on your plan\r\n<strong>8) </strong>Your priorities should direct profitable selling decisions of where to go and who to see\r\n<strong>9) </strong>Your priorities should crystallize which actions to take from those decisions\r\n<strong>10) </strong>Your priorities should be written down in action plans for the day, week, and month\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 10 - CONTROL</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_03c1_Point_10_Control.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 10: CONTROL</strong>\r\n<strong>1) </strong>Information control allows you to maximize the timing of your opportunities\r\n<strong>2) </strong>Consider the power and depth of information access today—working for or against you\r\n<strong>3) </strong>The Internet, computers, personal devices and data have revolutionized our world\r\n<strong>4) </strong>Your key is to make the best information you seek be the knowledge you own\r\n<strong>5) </strong>You are most valuable when you gain and use specialized (sales) knowledge for timing\r\n<strong>6) </strong>Having knowledge is not power—USING knowledge is power\r\n<strong>7) </strong>Learn the key structures and use the best tools to control your information life\r\n<strong>8) </strong>The first stage of I-Control is accessing raw information\r\n<strong>9) </strong>The second stage of I-Control is making that accessed information operational\r\n<strong>10) </strong>The third stage of I-Control is turning that operational information into sales and profits\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Big Banks &amp; Credit Cards</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_03c2_Point_10_Control_(story).mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 11 - COVERAGE</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_03d_Point_11_Coverage.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 11: COVERAGE</strong>\r\n<strong>1) </strong>Your coverage of your market area or account base is the platform of your income\r\n<strong>2) </strong>View your territory like a cash machine—load a lot in and take what you want out\r\n<strong>3) </strong>The scope of your coverage activities equals the “wide” leverage you generate\r\n<strong>4) </strong>You make more if you find business—you make less if your company finds it for you\r\n<strong>5) </strong>Determine the profile of your “best” buyers—and then close them at maximum price\r\n<strong>6) </strong>You must believe if you contact a lot of buyers that you will have plenty of sales to close\r\n<strong>7) </strong>A SalesMind can make a skilled sales call anywhere, anytime, and with anyone\r\n<strong>8) </strong>Determine and establish follow-up “triggers” to keep you in front of the best buyers\r\n<strong>9) </strong>Use your personal/company resources wisely\r\n<strong>10) </strong>Mix up how you contact people—phone, email, send, drop in—don’t be predictable\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Law 12 - ADJUSTMENT</h2>\r\n[video width="480" height="360" mp4="http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Part_03e_Point_12_Adjustment.mp4"][/video]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>KEY POINTS FOR LAW 12: ADJUSTMENT</strong>\r\n<strong>1) </strong>You must be willing to change and adjust constantly today to be the best at anything\r\n<strong>2) </strong>Have a very tight focus on what works in business and life—and what doesn’t\r\n<strong>3) </strong>Intelligent persistence is constantly adjusting your actions for optimal timing of sales\r\n<strong>4) </strong>Look around daily and you’ll see successful adjustments everywhere you can model\r\n<strong>5) </strong>Always ask “why should I adjust?” to keep the needed changes fresh in your mind\r\n<strong>6) </strong>Anticipate, innovate, and set expectations to help buyers or your competitor will\r\n<strong>7) </strong>Ask questions to adjust quantitatively (from numbers) and qualitatively (everything else)\r\n<strong>8) </strong>Some of your adjustments may be small by degree - some may be a total overhaul\r\n<strong>9) </strong>It takes faith, courage and determination to make real, lasting change\r\n<strong>10) </strong>Adjust in some downtime for yourself - you’ll have higher quality uptime if you do', 'The SalesMind Part 3', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '552-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-13 03:00:39', '2014-03-13 08:00:39', '', 552, 'http://localhost/dougtrenary.com/552-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
